rComments: He clearly wants his students to succeed. He is approachable and willing to help if needed. His lectures and expectations are clear and his use of group work breaks up the class. Enjoyed going to this class every week.

This course was fascinating. I did find the professor to be very sweet in regards to my accessibility needs. The course itself was incredibly intensive, and the weekly assignments, long lectures, readings and in class participation was exhaustive. I was surprised by how many things were due.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: loved the prof but hated the grading style of the whole course. never got feedback back on time for the next reading journal and he already told us it would be hard to get perfect on them anyway. tests were hard too

Also feedback was not individual, instead they posted a document with class feedback. (and didnt do it every week!!!!) Mark also said only 1-2 people can get perfect LOL what

Mark read off the lecture slides every week. If there was not weekly participation activities in lecture I would not have attended the lectures. Very dry lectures that I could have read in the comfort of my home.

rComments: Prof was very engaging and clear about the subject matter, which made lectures enjoyable.
